[SN]TITLE[SN]
Media stocks drag US markets lower

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Close): US stocks closed down after media companies suffered hefty falls.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Markets were also edgy ahead of key non-farm payroll figures which are out on Friday and will be studied for clues as to the strength of the US economy, and therefore the direction of interest rates.
The Dow Jones finished trading down 0.67% at 17,422.18.
The Nasdaq was down 1.62% at 5,056.44 and the broader S&P was 0.76% down at 2,083.81 poi
Shares in Disney dropped a further 2% having dived 9% on Wednesday following disappointing results.
Shares in 21st Century Fox lost 6.5% after the media conglomerate reported a 91% drop in profit on Wednesday.
Viacom, which owns Nickelodeon and Comedy Central, lost 13% after third-quarter revenues fell 10.6% to $3.06bn.
